                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="224400" author="mdiep" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2018 14:20:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is this still an issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="199807" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 07:23:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre snapshot needs to be triggered manually. In the lustre-initialization-1, nobody triggers Lustre snapshot, and there is node-provisioning-1 just before the lustre-initialization-1, the system should be clean when lustre-initialization-1. So I do not think it is related with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="189926" author="adilger" created="Tue, 28 Mar 2017 21:07:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fan Yong, are you sure this isn&apos;t caused by the snapshot patches?  Having multiple pools with the same name definitely seems like a snapshot problem.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have the same problem at home (with ldiskfs) when I make a &lt;tt&gt;dd&lt;/tt&gt; copy of the MDT to a backup device, and I try to mount the disk by label, if I don&apos;t change the label on the MDT backup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
